FBIS4-17258 "drsov078_u_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-078 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 Latvia Latvia Off U.S. Arms Export Ban List Latvia Off U.S. Arms Export Ban List LD2104170094 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1500 GMT 21 Apr 94 LD2104170094 Riga Radio Riga Network Latvian BFN [Text] From 4 April this year, the U.S. State Department will remove Latvia from the list of countries to which it is forbidden to export arms. The Latvian Foreign Ministry reports that the United States has officially announced that Latvia, Albania, Bulgaria, Cambodia, Estonia, and Romania are no longer to be included in the list of countries to which, observing the rules of international arms trade, the U.S. forbids the export of arms and defense equipment. This means that in future the United States will not require a licence for the export or import of defense material and defence services to Latvia.
